
    Its mentality is simple. Assume that you are in traffic and there is red light. You most likely don't switch-off your car engine. Because you know that very soon green light will light.

    The mentality behind the spinlocks is the same. Spinlocks works almost same as the normal mutexes, the only difference is:
    In mutexes a thread is taken off the CPU by the OS Scheduler (Forced Context Switching) 
    But in spin locks it continuously spins. (Busy waiting)







